# How Keyword Generation Works

AHU's search does prefix/contains matching and requires at least 3 characters. So scraper generating all 17,576 three-letter combos (aaa в†’ zzz) on first run which cover all companies available not generate keyword from scraped companies as you told me i think we will miss lot companies. then apply a simple rule per keyword:

- *0вЂ“1 results* в†’ skip it
- *2вЂ“160 results* в†’ scrape it
- *160+ results* в†’ expand to 4-letter variants and requeue

The 160 threshold exists because reCAPTCHA tokens expire in ~2 minutes, and each page takes ~12 seconds вЂ” so roughly 8 pages per token is the safe limit.

### Why not just scrape all pages of a big keyword directly?

why not scrape `"ind"` directly even if it has thousands of results, and just refresh the token when it expires?

The problem is cost. Each token refresh = one 2captcha API call. A keyword with 10,000 results has ~500 pages вЂ” that's potentially *500 token refreshes for just one keyword*. Across thousands of keywords, the bill explodes.

Instead, by expanding `"ind"` into `inda`, `indb`, `indc`... each chunk stays under 160 results, so *one token covers the entire chunk*. All the same data gets scraped, just through smaller targeted keywords вЂ” and total token usage drops from thousands to maybe 50вЂ“100.

Same data. Much cheaper.

## Database Design

Fully normalized SQLite schema. The `data_id` from AHU's HTML is used as the natural unique key, so re-scraping never creates duplicates. Keywords table makes the whole thing resumable вЂ” crash and restart, it picks up where it left off.

## Handling Rate Limits & Geo-Blocking

- *Proxies* вЂ” rotating datacenter Indonesian IPs only, loaded from `proxies.txt`
- *reCAPTCHA* вЂ” solved via 2captcha API, same proxy passed to the solver so IPs match
- *Fingerprinting* вЂ” canvas, audio, WebGL all randomized per session

## Configuration

*`.env`*

2CAPTCHA_API_KEY=key_here

*`proxies.txt`* вЂ” one proxy per line. More proxies = faster scraping + lower detection risk. Indonesian datacenter IPs recommended:
1.2.3.4:8080:user:password
5.6.7.8:8080:user:password

## Setup

Requires Python 3.11. Create a virtual environment:
python3.11 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt

## Install Chromium Browser
python -m patchright install chromium --with-deps

## Running It
source .venv/bin/activate
python main.py
